'''Dionisie Fotino''' was a [[Wallachia]]n historian and high ranking civil servant of [[Greeks|Greek]] origin.{{sfn|Boia|2001|p=86}} He is one of the first scholars to propose a [[Daco-Roman]] ancestry for the [[Romanians]] by stating, in his ''History of Old Dacia'' of 1818, that "the Romans and [[Dacians]], crossbreeding, created a distinct, mixed people" in [[Dacia Traiana]] province.{{sfn|Georgescu|1991|p=116}}

Fotinos (Photeinos, Gr. Φωτεινός ) hailed from the so-called [[Phanariote]] families within the [[Ottoman Empire]].

